{"lemma":"شَوْكَةٌ","slug":"شَوْكَةٌ","root":"ش.#.ك","root_slug":"ش-_-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-_-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَوْكَة","root":"شوك","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23359"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thorn, sting, prickle","tags":["singulative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tongue of a buckle","tags":["singulative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"arms and their points, clash of combatants, bravery, military power, power, greatness, pomp, majesty","tags":["singulative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fork (pronged eating utensil)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃaw.ka/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23359","headword_ar":"شَوْكَةٌ","root":"$wk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awokN","text_ar":"شَوْكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S &c.) [Hence various meanings here following; all of which seem to be tropical.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbatohumo $awokapu AlqanaA","text_ar":"اَصَابَتْهُمْ شَوْكَةُ القَنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The point of the spear hit, hurt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wounded, them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA. [There expl. only by the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"whY $bh AlAsnp","text_ar":"وهى شبه الاسنة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wahiYa $ibohu AlA^asin~api","text_ar":"وَهِىَ شِبْهُ الاَسِنَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as though relating to a pl. number.]) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA biAl$~awokapi","text_ar":"جَاوُوا بِالشَّوْكَةِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAl$~ajarapi","text_ar":"وَالشَّجَرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came with multitude"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of armed men"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awokapu AlEaqorabi","text_ar":"شَوْكَةُ العَقْرَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sting of the scorpion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awokapu","text_ar":"شَوْكَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaAy^iki","text_ar":"الحَايِكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The weaver's implement with which he makes the warp and the woof even:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:) i. e., (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~awokapu","text_ar":"الشَّوْكَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~iySiyapu","text_ar":"الصِّيصِيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~iySapu","text_ar":"الصِّيصَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) as having this meaning: ―         -b6-  and also as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The spur"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the cock. (O, TA.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~awokapu","text_ar":"الشَّوْكَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, O,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awokapu Alkat~aAni","text_ar":"شَوْكَةُ الكَتَّانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of clay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a moist state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made into a round form, and having its upper part pressed so that it becomes expanded, then"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prickles of the palm-tree are stuck into it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it dries;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"used for clearing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"combing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flax therewith:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O, K, TA:) mentioned by Az: and also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkat~aAni","text_ar":"الكَتَّانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uwaAkapu","text_ar":"شُوَاكَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awokapN","text_ar":"شَوْكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A weapon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weapons;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silaAHN","text_ar":"سِلَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA, and Ham p. 526;) as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN *uw $uwokapK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ ذُو شُوْكَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is a possessor of a weapon"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weapons;"},{"kind":"text","text":"though this admits of another rendering, as will be shown by what follows]: (TA:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpness"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: (K, TA:) or (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"point,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a weapon. (S, O.) ―         -b9-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vehemence of might"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of valour"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prowess,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K, TA,) in respect of fighting: (K, TA:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemence of encounter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"infliction of havock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement slaughter"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wounding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nikaAyapN","text_ar":"نِكَايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"effectiveness therein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] among the enemy: (K, TA:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength in weapons"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the use thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) and [simply] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"might."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 526.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahumo $awokapN","text_ar":"لَهُمْ شَوْكَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlHarobi","text_ar":"فِى الحَرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They have vehemence of might"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of valour"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prowess, in war"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa *uw $awokapK fiY AlEaduw~i","text_ar":"هُوَ ذُو شَوْكَةٍ فِى العَدُوِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has effectiveness in the infliction of havock among the enemy"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halum~a A_ilaY jihaAdK laA $awokapa fiyhi","text_ar":"هَلُمَّ اـِلَى جِهَادٍ لَا شَوْكَةَ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come to a war in the cause of religion wherein is no vehemence of might"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pilgrimage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b10-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain disease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plague,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pestilence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAEuwn","text_ar":"طَاعُون"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IDrd, O.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A redness that arises"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the body"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the face, and part of the body, and is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"said to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allayed by means of charms,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spells:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) because the sting of the scorpion, which is thus called, when it strikes a man, mostly produces redness. (A, TA.) ―         -b11-  [In one instance, in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awokapN","text_ar":"شَوْكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awikapN","text_ar":"شَوِكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an epithet applied to a tree.]"}],"source_refs":["S","O","TA","Lth","K","Msb","IDrd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}